org.svvrl.goal.core.aut.fsa
Class TransitionMonoid

java.lang.Object
  org.svvrl.goal.core.aut.fsa.TransitionMonoid

public class TransitionMonoid
extends java.lang.Object

This class provides methods to construct a monoid from a classic finite state automaton or a Büchi automaton. Let A be a Büchi automaton. Assume the states of A are s0, s1, …, sn. Let L(i, j) denote the strings of finite paths from si to sj and R(i, j) the strings of finite paths from si to sj through some accepting states. The transformation monoid of A is a set of n × n matrices {M1, M2, …, Mm} where each element can be TransitionMonoid.Value.ZERO or TransitionMonoid.Value.ONE. A matrix recognize some set of strings that have the same behavior in the automaton. Let L(M) denote the strings recognized by the matrix M. M[i, j] is TransitionMonoid.Value.ZERO if and only if L(M) ∩ L(i, j) = ∅. M[i, j] is TransitionMonoid.Value.ONE if and only if L(M) ⊆ L(i, j). The Büchi's transition monoid of A is a set of n × n matrices {M1, M2, …, Mm} where each element can be TransitionMonoid.Value.ZERO, TransitionMonoid.Value.ONE, or TransitionMonoid.Value.INFINITY. M[i, j] is TransitionMonoid.Value.ZERO if and only if L(M) ∩ L(i, j) = ∅. M[i, j] is TransitionMonoid.Value.ONE if and only if L(M) ⊆ L(i, j) - R(i, j). M[i, j] is TransitionMonoid.Value.INFINITY if and only if L(M) ⊆ R(i, j).

Author:
"Ming-Hsien Tsai"
